accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research with select materials restricted as noted in accordance with the terms of donation from the Laurance S. Rockefeller estate (January 2009). Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

Researchers interested in accessing audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The Rockefeller Archive Center has title, copyright, and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them, and has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Original order. Alphabetical, in series, primarily by subject/topic.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The 2001-2006 general files chronicle continued management of the philanthropic affairs of Laurance S. Rockefeller.

Over the years the Rockefeller family has been involved in virtually all aspects of modern philanthropy at the local, national and international levels through their foundation activities as well as their individual personal giving. Major interests include: physical and mental health, conservation, education, economics, international relations, medicine and science, politics, population, religion, social welfare, the visual and performing arts, cultural exchange programs, and economic and social development of underdeveloped areas. While Laurance S. Rockefeller naturally began to reduce his public schedule and activities in the later years of his life and career, the vast scope and breadth of his philanthropic interests continued in much of the same subject matter.

The general files primarily consist of correspondence, reports, pamphlets, memoranda, charters and certificates of incorporation, minutes and meeting records as well as documentation of contributions, finance and investment materials, real estate and properties, newspaper clippings, diaries, notebooks, calendars, and printed material.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Minimal processing. Records primarily remain in original folders.
